# üñ•Ô∏è Headless Display Setup

This documents how I configured a virtual display on my Linux Mint server using a dummy HDMI plug and `xrandr`.

## Why?

Without a monitor connected, the NVIDIA GPU doesn't activate. The dummy HDMI simulates a connected display so that I can:

- Enable GPU acceleration
- Use remote desktop if needed vis Rustdeck
- Let services recognize a display

## Commands Used

```bash
xrandr --newmode "1440p"  241.50  2560 2728 3000 3440  1440 1443 1448 1493 -hsync +vsync
xrandr --addmode HDMI-0 "1440p"
xrandr --output HDMI-0 --mode "1440p"
